Criticism by Russian authorities of their Navy arose quickly following the rescue.
Accident notification was delayed as in the Kursk tragedy.
Putin ordered an investigation.
Russian rescuers damaged their underwater robotic vehicle during the rescue attempt making it inoperable.
When the British rescue vehicle arrived by air there was no equipment to unload it.
Russia is considering purchasing a robotic Scorpio or Panther for underwater rescue operations.
Adm. Kuroyedov, head of the Russian Navy, was fired and replaced by Adm. Masorin.
Masorin has been charged with improving the Navy.
Operation errors by the crew were cited as causing the accident.
